Executive Profile
Todd M. Abbrecht  Head of Private Equity, Thomas H. Lee Partners, L.P.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 11 Board Members in 11 different organizations across 17 different industries.See Board Relationships48--
Background

		Mr. Todd M. Abbrecht serves as Head of Private Equity at Thomas H. Lee Partners, L.P. He was Managing Director at the firm. Mr. Abbrecht joined the firm in 1992 and served as its Vice President. He has been involved in the execution of firm's investments in the consumer and healthcare space. Prior to that, he served in the Mergers and Acquisitions department at Credit Suisse First Boston focused primarily on financial institutions. He has been a Director of Fogo de Chao, ... Inc. since May 2012, inVentiv Health Inc. since August 2010, Simmons Company since December 2003, Warner Chilcott Holdings Company III, Limited since November 8, 2004, Party City Holdco Inc., since July 2012, inVentiv Group Holdings, Inc. since August 2010 and THL since August 2010. He serves as a Director of CSafe Global, Professional Physical Therapy, PCI Pharma Services, Curo Health Services, Healthcare Staffing Services, Warner Chilcott Corporation, Intermedix Corporation, MTHL Bedding Holding Co., Achievement Technologies Inc., CelPage, Inc. and Sundari Inc. He served as the Chairman of the Board of Directors at Party City Holdings Inc. and also has been its Director since July 2012. He served as the Chairman of Party City Holdco Inc. He served as a Director of Aramark Corporation since January 2007 until February 01, 2017. He served as a Director of National Waterworks Holdings, Inc., since November 22, 2002, B-R 31 Ice Cream Co., Ltd., Dunkin' Brands Group, Inc., from 2006 to June 22, 2012, Warner Chilcott Plc from November 8, 2004 to November 9, 2012, HD Supply Waterworks, Ltd. since November 22, 2002, Hilltop Holdings Inc. from August 2000 to January 2005, Simmons Bedding Company LLC since December 2003 and Michael Foods, Inc. since November 2003. He served as a Director of Affordable Residential Communities, Inc. Mr. Abbrecht holds a B.S.E. in Finance from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania and an M.B.A. degree from the Harvard Graduate School of Business Administration.Read Full Background




